UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. SECURITY FIRST NATIONAL BANK OF LOS ANGELES et al., Appellees. No. 8082. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 6, 1936. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and E. H. Mitchell, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Los Angeles, Cal. Farrand . & Slosson, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellees.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
